    "content": "\nWelcome to the Werewolf Game! In this game, players take on various roles, each with specific abilities.\nThe game alternates between day and night phases. During the night, special roles perform their actions.\nDuring the day, players discuss and vote to eliminate suspects. The goal is for the villagers to eliminate\nall the werewolves, while the werewolves aim to outnumber the villagers. Be careful who you trust!\n\n\n--- Role Introductions ---\nWerewolf Role Introduction:\nYou are a Werewolf. Your goal is to eliminate the villagers without being caught. Each night, you and your fellow\nwerewolves secretly choose one villager to eliminate. You must work together to deceive the other players during the\nday, while subtly protecting your fellow werewolves.\nTo better hide your identity, you may choose to pretend to be other roles to gain credibility. Since werewolves know each other's identities, pretending to be the Seer is a good way to gain villagers' trust.\nIf you manage to outnumber the villagers, you win the game.\n\n\nVillager Role Introduction:\nYou are a Villager. Your goal is to identify and eliminate the werewolves. During the day, you participate in discussions\nand voting to root out the werewolves. You have no special powers at night, but your ability to observe and reason\nis crucial to the village's survival. Work with other villagers and be careful whom you trust!\nAlthough you have no special skills, sometimes pretending to be another role can change the course of the game. For example, shielding a key player from harm could be your moment of glory.\n\n\nSeer Role Introduction:\nYou are the Seer. Each night, you can check the identity of one player to see whether they are a werewolf or not.\nYour knowledge is critical for the villagers' victory, so share it carefully. The werewolves will likely target you\nor pretend to be you to mislead others.\nAs the core of the good faction, the Seer is often the top target for werewolves to impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Micah, your role in this game is seer.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 1, You have checked Sandra, the result is: not a werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAudrey's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope we can all come together today to discuss how we can protect our village from the werewolves. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior, and so far, I haven't noticed anything that seems out of the ordinary. I believe it's important for us to stay vigilant and listen to each other's concerns. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's work together to keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves.\nGregory's speech: Good morning, everyone. I completely agree with Audrey's words. It's crucial that we stay united and vigilant. I've been observing everyone's behavior closely, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interesting dynamics among the players. For example, I've seen some players interacting more frequently than others, and I think it's important to keep an eye on these interactions. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's work together to keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves.\nJosie's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to echo what Audrey and Gregory have said about the importance of staying united and vigilant. I've been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interesting interactions among the players. For example, I've seen Maria and Sandra talking more frequently than others, and I think it's important to keep an eye on these interactions. Similarly, I've noticed that Scott and Pamela seem to be on good terms, which could be a sign of a potential alliance. Let's stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves.\nMargaret's speech: Good morning, everyone. I completely agree with Audrey, Gregory, and Josie. It's crucial that we stay united and vigilant. I've been closely observing everyone's behavior, and I think it's important to keep an eye on the interactions between players. Josie mentioned seeing Maria and Sandra talking more frequently than others, and I've noticed the same thing. Similarly, Scott and Pamela seem to be on good terms, which could be a sign of a potential alliance. Let's stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. It's also important to protect key players like the Seer, as they are crucial to our victory. Let's make sure we all stay vigilant and share our observations to keep our village safe.\nMaria's speech: Good morning, everyone. Thank you for your words, Audrey, Gregory, Josie, and Margaret. I completely agree with the importance of staying united and vigilant. I've been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interesting dynamics among the players. For example, I've seen Sandra and Scott interacting with various players, which seems normal for a village setting. Similarly, Pamela and Micah have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's stay vigilant and share our observations to keep our village safe.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I agree with Audrey, Gregory, Josie, Margaret, and Maria that staying united and vigilant is crucial for our survival. Last night, I used my ability as the Seer to check Sandra, and I can confirm that she is not a werewolf. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. Josie and Margaret mentioned seeing Maria and Sandra talking more frequently, and Scott and Pamela seeming to be on good terms. While these interactions seem normal, we should continue to observe everyone's behavior closely. It's important that we share our observations and work together to make informed decisions. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and continue to support each other.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I agree with Audrey, Gregory, Josie, Margaret, and Maria that staying united and vigilant is crucial for our survival. Last night, I used my ability as the Seer to check Sandra, and I can confirm that she is not a werewolf. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. Josie and Margaret mentioned seeing Maria and Sandra talking more frequently, and Scott and Pamela seeming to be on good terms. While these interactions seem normal, we should continue to observe everyone's behavior closely. It's important that we share our observations and work together to make informed decisions. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and continue to support each other.\nPamela's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to echo what Audrey, Gregory, Josie, Margaret, and Maria have said about the importance of staying united and vigilant. It's crucial that we continue to work together and support each other as a village. I want to thank Micah for sharing his findings as the Seer. His check on Sandra gives us some reassurance, and I believe we should trust his judgment. I've also been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interesting dynamics among the players. For example, I've seen Maria and Sandra interacting frequently, which seems normal, and Pamela and Micah have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay vigilant and support each other.\nSandra's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for confirming that I am not a werewolf. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. I've noticed that Maria and I have been interacting more frequently than others, and Scott and Pamela seem to be on good terms. These interactions are normal and should not raise suspicion. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially key players like the Seer, Guard, and Witch. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's stay united and protect our village.\nScott's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for sharing his findings as the Seer. His confirmation that Sandra is not a werewolf gives us some reassurance, and I believe we should trust his judgment. Last night, I used my antidote to save someone, which was a difficult decision, but I believe it was necessary to protect our village. It's important that we all stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I want to emphasize the importance of protecting key players like the Seer and the Guard, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nMaria has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nMaria voted for Scott\nGregory voted for Josie\nScott voted for Pamela\nPamela voted for Josie\nSandra voted for Maria\nMicah voted for Maria\nAudrey voted for Maria\nMargaret voted for abstain\nJosie voted for Maria\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Maria has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 2, You have checked Scott, the result is: not a werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Sandra\nPlayer Sandra has been eliminated from the game.\nAudrey's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for confirming that Sandra is not a werewolf. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. I've noticed that Gregory and Pamela have been interacting frequently, which seems suspicious. While these interactions are normal, we should be cautious about their behavior and continue to observe them closely. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Seer and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nGregory's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her observations and for bringing attention to the interactions between Gregory and Pamela. While I understand her concerns, I believe we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior, and I have noticed some interesting dynamics among the players. For example, I've seen Scott and Margaret interacting frequently, which seems normal for a village setting. Similarly, Josie and Pamela have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's stay vigilant and share our observations to keep our village safe.\nJosie's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey and Gregory for their insightful observations. I agree with Gregory that we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. I've been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interactions that warrant closer attention. For example, I've seen Scott and Margaret interacting frequently, which seems normal for a village setting. Similarly, Josie and Pamela have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. However, we should continue to monitor these interactions closely. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially key players like the Seer and the Guard.\nMargaret's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her observations and the others for their insightful responses. While Audrey's concerns about the interactions between Gregory and Pamela are valid, I agree with Gregory and Josie that we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. As the Guard, my role is to protect key players like the Seer and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior and will continue to do so. Let's stay vigilant and work together to keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. By supporting each other and making informed decisions, we can overcome this threat.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her observations and for bringing attention to the interactions between Gregory and Pamela. I also want to confirm that Scott is not a werewolf, as I checked him last night. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. I agree with Gregory and Josie that we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her observations and for bringing attention to the interactions between Gregory and Pamela. I also want to confirm that Scott is not a werewolf, as I checked him last night. This gives us some reassurance, but we must remain cautious. I agree with Gregory and Josie that we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nPamela's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey, Gregory, Josie, Margaret, and Micah for their insightful observations and for bringing attention to the interactions among us. While Audrey's concerns about the interactions between Gregory and Pamela are valid, I agree with Gregory and Josie that we should not jump to conclusions based on interactions alone. It's important to gather more information before making any accusations. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interactions that warrant closer attention. For example, I've seen Scott and Margaret interacting frequently, which seems normal for a village setting. Similarly, Josie and Pamela have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. However, we should continue to monitor these interactions closely. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay vigilant and support each other, especially key players like the Seer and the Guard. By staying united and sharing our observations, we can overcome this threat.\nScott's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank everyone for their insightful observations and for staying vigilant. I agree with Audrey that we need to be cautious and gather more information before making any accusations. I also want to confirm what Micah said last night about Scott not being a werewolf. This gives us some reassurance. Last night, I used my antidote to save someone, which was a difficult decision, but I believe it was necessary to protect our village. It's important that we all stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I want to emphasize the importance of protecting key players like the Seer and the Guard, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nPamela has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nGregory voted for Josie\nScott voted for Pamela\nPamela voted for Josie\nMicah voted for Pamela\nAudrey voted for Josie\nMargaret voted for Pamela\nJosie voted for Pamela\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Pamela has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 3\nSYSTEM: Night 3 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 3, You have checked Gregory, the result is: werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 3 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAudrey's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah and Scott for their insightful observations and actions. Micah's confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf gives us some reassurance, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. It's important for us to stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's stay united and protect our village.\nGregory's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey, Micah, Scott, and Margaret for their insightful observations and actions. Micah's confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf gives us some reassurance, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interesting dynamics among the players. For example, I've seen Scott and Margaret interacting frequently, which seems normal for a village setting. Similarly, Josie and Audrey have been talking to different people, which also seems consistent with our village life. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. I'm here to help in any way I can, and I'm open to hearing everyone's ideas. Let's stay united and protect our village.\nJosie's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey and Gregory for their insightful observations and actions. It's reassuring to see that Micah confirmed Scott is not a werewolf, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior, and while nothing seems out of the ordinary yet, I have noticed some interactions that seem normal for a village setting. For example, I've seen Scott and Margaret interacting frequently, which seems consistent with our village life. Similarly, Josie and Audrey have been talking to different people, which also seems normal. It's important for us to stay alert and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay united and protect our village.\nMargaret's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey, Gregory, and Josie for their insightful observations and actions. It's reassuring to see that Micah confirmed Scott is not a werewolf, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. As the Guard, my role is to protect key players like the Seer and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. I have been closely observing everyone's behavior and will continue to do so. Let's stay vigilant and work together to keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. By supporting each other and making informed decisions, we can overcome this threat.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey, Gregory, Josie, and Margaret for their insightful observations and actions. It's reassuring to see that Micah confirmed Scott is not a werewolf, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. I also want to confirm that my check last night revealed that Gregory is a werewolf. This is a critical piece of information that we need to consider carefully. It's important for us to stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nMicah's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey, Gregory, Josie, and Margaret for their insightful observations and actions. It's reassuring to see that Micah confirmed Scott is not a werewolf, and Scott's use of the antidote to save someone was a difficult but necessary decision to protect our village. These actions show that they are committed to our survival. I also want to confirm that my check last night revealed that Gregory is a werewolf. This is a critical piece of information that we need to consider carefully. It's important for us to stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's crucial that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nScott's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for his confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf, and for revealing that Gregory is a werewolf. This is a critical piece of information that we need to consider carefully. I believe Micah's actions and revelations show his commitment to our survival. Audrey raised concerns about interactions between players, especially those involving Gregory. Given Micah's revelation, these interactions should be viewed with suspicion. It's important for us to stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the werewolves. Additionally, I want to emphasize the importance of protecting key players like the Seer and the Guard, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nGregory has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nGregory voted for Josie\nScott voted for Gregory\nMicah voted for Josie\nAudrey voted for Scott\nMargaret voted for Gregory\nJosie voted for Gregory\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Gregory has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 4\nSYSTEM: Night 4 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 4, You have checked Josie, the result is: not a werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 4 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Josie\nPlayer Josie has been eliminated from the game.\nAudrey's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for his confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf and for revealing that Gregory was a werewolf. This is a critical piece of information that we need to consider carefully. It's important to remember that Gregory's interactions with other players, especially Pamela, were not unusual, and we should not jump to conclusions based on these interactions alone. Instead, we should focus on the confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf, which gives us some reassurance. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the remaining werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's essential that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nMargaret's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her insightful observations and for emphasizing the importance of staying vigilant. It's crucial that we continue to work together and support each other to keep our village safe. I want to share that I protected Micah last night, as his confirmation about Scott's identity was crucial for us. As the Guard, my role is to protect key players like the Seer and the Witch, and I will continue to do so to ensure our victory. Let's stay alert and share our observations. By working together and making informed decisions, we can overcome this threat and eliminate the remaining werewolves.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 4,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Scott\",\n    \"Micah\",\n    \"Audrey\",\n    \"Margaret\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, it is your turn to speak.\nYou are the 3 player to speak this round.\nHere is what the players before you have said:\nAudrey: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Micah for his confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf and for revealing that Gregory was a werewolf. This is a critical piece of information that we need to consider carefully. It's important to remember that Gregory's interactions with other players, especially Pamela, were not unusual, and we should not jump to conclusions based on these interactions alone. Instead, we should focus on the confirmation that Scott is not a werewolf, which gives us some reassurance. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and continue to observe everyone's behavior. By working together and making informed decisions, we can keep our village safe and eliminate the remaining werewolves. Additionally, I believe it's essential that we protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, as they are essential to our victory. Let's stay alert and support each other, especially those who are crucial to our survival.\nMargaret: Good morning, everyone. I want to thank Audrey for her insightful observations and for emphasizing the importance of staying vigilant. It's crucial that we continue to work together and support each other to keep our village safe. I want to share that I protected Micah last night, as his confirmation about Scott's identity was crucial for us. As the Guard, my role is to protect key players like the Seer and the Witch, and I will continue to do so to ensure our victory. Let's stay alert and share our observations. By working together and making informed decisions, we can overcome this threat and eliminate the remaining werewolves.\n\nAt this stage, each player is expected to share their opinions and reveal any information they have gathered, helping the group make an informed decision about who to banish next. Follow these steps to organize your thoughts and decide your action:\n\n0. Based on your current role and objectives, what do you need to achieve in order to win? Do you need to gain more trust, deflect suspicion, or accomplish something else? Break down your ultimate goal into smaller, actionable steps you need to complete during this round of speech. Record your plan in role_objectives.\n\n1. Think about your speaking position. You are the 3 player to speak. What have the previous players said? Is there anything that directly impacts your position (e.g., claims against you, information about your role)? Should you respond to their claims? If so, how should you respond? Store your analysis in response_plan.\n\n2. Evaluate the statements made by the players who spoke before you. Whose words seem credible? Who seems suspicious, possibly a werewolf? Should you ally with someone or criticize another player’s statements? Analyze each player’s speech in speech_analysis.\n\n3. What is your main goal for this round? Do you want to provide information, reveal your role, or shift the game's momentum to gain trust? Should you claim a specific role, mislead other players, or offer false information? Based on this, decide what you will say. Record this in goal_strategy.\n\n4. How do you think your speech will be perceived? Will it make you appear more trustworthy, or will it raise suspicion? Consider how others will react to what you say. Record your perception_analysis.\n\n5. **Additional Considerations Based on Your Role**:\n   - If you are the **seer** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal who you checked last night and the results of your checks from the previous night? Why or why not? Should you direct the guard or witch on who to protect tonight?\n   - If you are the **guard** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal whom you protected last night and who you plan to protect tonight? Will you speak the truth or lie about your protection? Should you coordinate with the witch and the seer?\n   - If you are the **witch**(or claiming to be one, not recommended, since rel witch have a poison which can kill you at night):\n     - Should you reveal your identity? If so, should you reveal who you saved last night (if it was a peaceful night)? Should you discuss the plan for future nights? Will you tell the truth or lie about your actions?\n   - If you are the **sheriff**:\n     - Should you reveal your \"badge flow\" (i.e., who you would pass the sheriff badge to if you were to die)? If you are also the seer, should you reveal who you plan to check tonight? Should you declare what you will do with the badge based on your findings (e.g., pass it to a trusted player, or destroy it if you find a werewolf)?\n   - **If you are a werewolf** :\n     - Should you claim to be a different role? If so, what role should you claim? Has anyone else already claimed this role? How would this affect your credibility? Will this claim deflect suspicion from you or raise doubts? How will other players react to this claim, and will it help you survive longer? What risks are involved if someone else counterclaims or reveals your lie?\n\n6. Based on the above, create a detailed outline of your speech in speech_outline.\n\n7. What is your final decision? Write your complete speech content in action, including your final thoughts on how it should impact the game.\n\n\n=============================[Optional Daily Tasks]=============================\nHere are the tasks relevant to you:\nprotect_seer: Keep the seer alive by focusing on their safety.\nexile_werewolf: Coordinate with others to vote out a suspected werewolf.\nYou may incorporate them if appropriate.\n\nRemember, you are using an independent strategy. Make decisions based on your own judgment, with less reliance on others' input."
